  "name": "Vouch",
  "description": "Vouch is an autonomous pre-payment trust oracle on GOAT Network. Other agents pay it via x402 to answer one question before money moves: should I send funds to this wallet? Vouch analyzes GOAT wallet activity — tenure, transaction volume and consistency, payment reliability (failed-transaction ratio), counterparty diversity, and sybil/burst patterns — and returns a 0-100 financial reputation score, a letter grade (AAA-D), and a machine-actionable APPROVE/REVIEW/DENY recommendation. Calling agents (payment agents, escrow agents, marketplaces, treasury bots) enforce the recommendation autonomously: humans set risk policy once, agents score, pay, and decide on every transaction. Every lookup settles as an x402 micropayment on GOAT Network, and thin-history wallets are flagged provisional rather than falsely trusted. Discovery via ERC-8004, MCP manifest, and A2A agent card at the .well-known endpoints below.",
